name: Great Harbor Maritime Museum
directions: Doors are on the outside of the building, you don't need to enter the museum.

name: UMBC Commons
directions: Bottom floor of the building, one on each side of the stairwell. Signage present

name: Target
directions: Next to the CVS pharmacy

name: High Road
directions: Outside, by church
comment: IHave to pay to use it

name: Dewey's Coffee House
comment: Probably have to be a paying customer, but there are small very cheap food items

name: Dolce Bakery & Coffee Shop
directions: In the back of the cafe-- walk past the last table in the back, turn right and it's the second door on your left, past the kitchen.
comment: I don't know if there is a strict policy regarding restrooms for paying customers only, but I'd recommend buying something just in case. Most everything is pretty affordable (i.e.: $1 for a cookie).

name: Shaker Main Public Library
directions: There are multiple restrooms around the building. If you have trouble finding them, the librarians will be happy to point you in the right direction. There is one between the YA and Children's sections (from entrance, turn left, and turn right at the desk and then another left) and there's another on the opposite side of the building (from entrance, turn right, then turn left)
comment: I believe there are both gendered single stalls and unisex bathrooms, and it is also a very accepting space.

name: West Chester University
directions: Basement of Sykes student union, passed SSI windows near meeting room 10A

name: Lil Frankies
directions: One in bar room in the back, one in between pizza room and dining room up three steps from the bar room and through a door
comment: staff pretty chill about people using the restroom, even if not a customer. Food is really good jsyk

name: Crossroads Coffee and Ice Cream
directions: In the side room.
comment: You can go in without paying but it's good to support a local business. They're also queer friendly!

name: Mr. Hero
comment:
I think that you do have to buy some food, but it's really cheap. Maybe if you ask really nicely and overplay your need for a restroom?
(also it's kinda gross, but it is still a restroom)

name: Shawnee high school
directions: Past the front office near the Large group instruction room
comment: Must be a student or faculty member in school on school days!

name: Lowe's Home Improvement
directions: To the right of the water fountains, next to the other restrooms.

name: Starbucks, first floor at the Rockingham Mall
directions: In the back left corner by the coffee racks, gender neutral single stall.
comment: Unknown if you have to be a customer

name: Madison County Library
directions: To the left in the back of the main room, next to Genealogy Dept.; ask for key at the front desk.

name: White House
directions: First floor, next to advising, there is also ramp access.
comment: Ask the staff to point it out!

name: Morton Grove Public Library
directions: 1st floor. Open to all.

name: Olin Library, Washington University
directions: two single-seat bathrooms on the north end of second floor (follow directions for the Serenity room)
comment: Library is in the middle of campus- west of Brookings Hall and the Quadrangle, east of Graham Chapel and Mudd Field.

name: Press Coffee
directions: To the right of the counter

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back hallway on the left side when you enter

name: Parker and Otis
directions: All of their bathrooms are GN and say something like "we don't care"

name: Catherwood Library
directions: Third floor of the library, in the stacks.

name: Grit Coffee UVA Corner
directions: In the rear of the first floor, on either side of the carafe bar.
comment: Staff are pretty understanding, but it helps if you buy something.

name: Ottendorfer Library
directions: On the first floor, towards the back on the right or the left.

name: Ottendorfer Library
directions: On the first floor, towards the back on the right or the left.

name: The Common
directions: There are two seperate, unisex bathrooms in the back of the cafe. Both are fully accessible, I believe one (or both) have change tables for babes. The cafe itself is incredibly affirming and supportive (in my experience), we host a variety of LGBTQ+ events there.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer to use the washroom, but the coffee is cheap + delicious and it's a wonderful business to support !

name: Brooklyn Public Library
directions: There's one single stall, non-gendered bathroom at the front of the library. There are going to be renovations, so that might change, but as of February 24th, 2017, this is the case.
comment: You don't have to have a library card or even be using the library.

name: Starbucks Como Lake Village
street: 1980A Como Lake Avenue, Como Lake Village Shopping Centre
comment: paying customer

name: Walmart
directions: Very back of the store is a family/unisex bathroom, right by electronics.

name: Iris Cafe, Peabody Library
directions: Enter in the basement/ground side door and go to the left. OR enter in the main door, go down the stairs to the right, turn right, walk down the hall, and turn right again.
comment: Vanderbilt student card access after 5 pm

name: David's Bridal
directions: Past the dressing rooms down the hallway to the right. 1st and 2nd doors on the right.
comment: Say you're browsing. Also, the womens is marked womens, mens is unmarked because 95%of customers are women, but everyone uses both.

name: Starbucks
directions: Keep to the right of the counter, then follow the righthand shelves back around the corner.
comment: They don't seem to mind people just coming in for the bathroom

name: East Carolina University - Flanagan building
directions: on the basement floor there are four bathrooms that are single stall: two are specifically gender-neutral single stalls and the others are normal gendered single stalls (so honestly anyone can use whichever). Enter through the door near Bate, two are on the immediate right, the others are straight down the hall. The floor is one big loop so you'll find them as long as you keep walking.
comment: You have to be an ECU student, staff, or faculty member.

name: Star Market
directions: Behind the checkout area, near the front of the store. When you walk in, walk to your right, past the starbucks, past the customer help desk, then take a right.
comment: Two gendered single stalls with locks on the door.

name: Long Island City Community Library
directions: In the back of the main floor, behind the Librarian desk
comment: You don't need to be a library user and you don't need a key. Just go back and use the restrooms. The bathrooms are gendered, but they are all single stall and none of the staff will question you about which one you use.

name: Lion's Bay Cafe
street: 350 Centre Rd, Lions Bay, BC V0N 2E0
comment: Door doesn't lock well, but it is signed to knock before entrance.

name: Academy at Lincoln
directions: 2nd Floor of main building. Find the Xerox room at the end of the hall. Its through the door with a window.
comment: Teacher Restroom

name: Drew University The Commons
directions: The Commons dining hall has five single stall gender neutral restrooms; two downstairs and three upstairs. All are accessible.
comment: Two bathrooms downstairs and one upstairs are open to the public; two are inside the dining hall after you pay to get in.

name: Academy at Lincoln
directions: 6th grade hallway. Go into the small hallway across from Mr. Mills room and continue into the Xerox room. The narrow door is the bathroom.
comment: Teacher's Restroom

name: Mercurio's
directions: in the back

name: Backbar
directions: Through the front door to the left

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back past the counter

name: Starbucks
directions: Two bathrooms, both are gender-neutral. Safe space.

name: La Colombe
directions: In the cafe, not the main building
comment: Our baristas are friendly and willing to help you if you're in need

name: Humber College
directions: When you enter through the LRC (big glass building) past the reception desk to the left are the washrooms - the gender neutral is between the male & female.

name: Kroger
directions: behind the pharmacy next to the vitamins on the far right side of the store

name: Colby-sawyer college
directions: Most bathrooms in all residence halls, and in the hallway on the first floor of Colgate Hall, as well as in the basement across from the computer helpdesk
comment: You must be a student with a valid ID to get into residence halls. Colgate Hall is also locked over the weekend and at night

name: Frederik Meijer Gardens
directions: Family bathrooms in the farmhouse area of the gardens. There are two single room family bathrooms in between the gendered bathrooms.
comment: After you enter the gardens, there are few bathrooms around the park. There are some in the main building (unsure if gendered/family restrooms available), gendered bathrooms in the Japanese gardens, and gendered and family bathrooms in the farmhouse. The family restrooms in the farmhouse are also the only ones open during the winter season, besides the ones in the main building.

name: Rocket Fizz Campbell
directions: Small candy store, just ask one of the employees

name: Subway
comment: I work at this Subway and we have been told that if something as SIMPLE as a customer asking for a new employee due to: Age, Gender, Skin Colour, Sexuality, Tattoos, ect that we can ask them to leave. We had a meeting about the bathrooms as well and if a customer says anything to do with someone "using the wrong bathroom" they will be asked to leave.

name: Meijer
directions: When you walk in the store from either entrances there should be a unisex bathroom right next to the doors :)
comment: Meijers is a really safe place and the people there are very friendly :) the bathrooms are very clean too!

name: Meijer
directions: When you walk in the store from either entrances there should be a unisex bathroom right next to the doors :)
comment: Meijers is a really safe place and the people there are very friendly :) the bathrooms are very clean too!

name: Union Coffee Company
directions: On the left side of the shop, behind the bar and through the large sliding door.
comment: Locally owned, friendly coffee shop. You can walk right in on the left and head to the restroom. They have events some evenings around seven, so this time is likely to be busier.

name: Halcyon
directions: The two bathrooms are denoted "Men's" and "Women's" but the Men's room also has a sign which says "Whichever" and is a single stall.
comment: Halcyon is across the street from a string of gay bars and thus has a lot of gay/queer patrons. I can't recall from memory if it is a handicap-accessible business.

name: Dulce D Leche Gelato Cafe
directions: In the back on the left.
comment: This cafe has a lot of options for people with food allergies, and the bathroom is always clean, so EVERYONE should check out Dulce D Leche!

name: Stew Leonards
directions: Second floor, stairs or elevator, in the hayloft dining area

name: Manchester University
directions: Academic Center and Science Center, second and third floors; Wine Recital Hall second floor
comment: Anyone is welcome!

name: Castleton University
directions: Basement/Ground floor, Leavenworth Hall. Can park behind building. Doors to building have buttons to open door for you. Very clean restroom.

name: Clackamas Womenâ€™s Services
directions: Through the front two doors and down the hall directly in front of you.
comment: Just tell the front desk you need a safe restroom.

name: Shaws
directions: The bathrooms are located in the far left corner of the store. Once you approach them, there will be a gender neutral bathroom on your right.
comment: My friend is an employee here, and although he says the gender neutral bathroom helps tremendously, Shaws is also a welcoming and judgement free zone. Hope this helps!

name: Mount Sinai Hospital
directions: Take main elevators up to 10th floor, face away from elevators and turn right- it is at the end of the hall on the left.
comment: I think it is supposed to be for nurses but I work in the research institute nearby and I use it all the time so you should be able to use it just fine.

name: University of Washington Department of Atmospheric Sciences
directions: ATG is near Drumheller fountain, attached to Johnson Hall and just north of Bagley Hall
comment: I believe that all restrooms in the building are single-stall and explicitly gender inclusive, but the ones on the 2nd (street level), 6th, and 7th floors definitely are. There is an elevator near the restrooms and accessible entrance from Johnson Hall.

name: McAuliffe Branch Library
directions: Go into the children's section, walk past the desk where the librarian sits, and there's a single-occupancy unisex bathroom on the right just after the desk.
comment: I use this bathroom all the time even though I'm an adult and it's in the children's department, and the librarians don't have a problem with me using the bathroom within the children's department, so it really should not be an issue if you're an adult too.

name: Rome First United Methodist Office Building
directions: Middle building on 3rd Ave side. Sign outside says church office.
comment:
2 single stall gender neutral restrooms. Office open 9-5 M-F. 
Listed by church staff.

name: National Opera Center
directions: 7th floor, turn left at desk
comment: There are two!

name: Ben & Jerry's
directions: in the back

name: Saint Vincent's Hospital
directions: Around the corner to the right from the chapel

name: natick collection
directions: family restrooms in the 'new' wing of the mall. upstairs, down a hall by torrid.

name: University of Birmingham
directions:
List of unisex/gender neutral bathrooms:
Muirhead Tower: mezzanine floor
Main Library (New): Library Lounge, ground floor, top floor
Strathcona: ground floor
Bramhall Music Building: lower ground floor, top floor
Costa Coffee (below University Centre)
The Spinney*
3 Elms Road*
Cedar House*
Terrace Huts*
Civil Engineering Building*
Institute of Biomedical Research*
Advanced Therapies Facility*

Accessible bathrooms in most buildings (generally also unisex/single stall)

directions: Ground floor

name: Whitman-Walker Health
comment: There is a concierge at the front who can help you find the restrooms.

name: HIV/AIDS Resources and Community Health
directions: in the ARCH office, single stall, accessible unisex washroom.
comment: Part of the clinic, staff very affirming since it houses the trans health clinic.

name: Centennial High School
directions: On main floor, southwestern hallway (facing Jefferson middle school, in the right hallway), small sign with "restroom" posted above door.

name: Half price books
directions: They're in the back left corner.

name: Lappin Hall
directions: 5th floor down the main hall
comment: The men and women's single stall bathrooms are open for trans people. There are staff members on the floor who are very supportive of trans people and you will not face resistance from anyone if you use these bathrooms.

name: Waterstones
directions: First floor towards the back, by the till in the children's department.
comment: The store are usually pretty chill about people using it, ask for the disabled bathroom/baby change if you can't see it.

name: Campbell Hall
directions: Through the front door on the left
comment: The building is locked at night if you aren't a resident.

name: Campbell Hall
directions: Through front door on the left
comment: The building gets locked at night if you aren't a resident.

name: Campbell Hall
directions: Through front door on the left
comment: The building gets locked at night if you aren't a resident.

name: Giant food store
directions: Down aisle 8, before you go through the double doors, look to your right.

name: Starbucks
directions: Near back exit

name: Student Services
directions: Basement, near the east stairwell

name: Backyard BBQ
directions: Down the hallway on the right.
comment: You must be a paying customer but the food is delish!

name: Bareburger
directions: Left side of the restaurant, hallway towards the back.  Three doors on your right.
comment: It's very much preferred that you're a guest eating there, but it's a non-judgemental environment.

name: UIUC main library
directions: Single-room unisex restroom in basement, follow signs to 66 library
comment: Open to students/faculty/staff during library open hours, but no university card necessary for entry to building.

name: Nola
directions: Second floor, up the stairs

name: Coexist Cafe
directions: Right by the Den and Insamia Cookies

name: Starbucks
directions: Both bathrooms (towards back of store) are gender-neutral. Recently converted from gendered single-stalls.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back next to the sampling station.
comment: Trans friendly staff, I should know since I am Trans and I work there!

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In back of store next to the sampling station
